The evidence with the title 'America's Affordable Health Choices Act of 2009 - wikipedia ' says The 2003 legislation only covered end-of-life counseling for terminally ill patients, which the Republican Charles Grassley supported. Grassley said that the 2009 end-of-life counseling would "pull the plug on grandma" and that "you shouldn't have counseling at the end of life, you should have done that 20 years before," ... 
